description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: 37.5 per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a motivated, dedicated and innovative Physiotherapist to join our Musculoskeletal Outpatients Team. We are looking for a Physiotherapist with specialist skills and an established specialist interest in MSK patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to support the wider team and assist in the development of your colleagues within this environment. Therefore, ability to work as part of a team, leadership skills and experience of supervising staff/students are essential criteria. In return, you will be supported by a well established and highly experienced team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be able to demonstrate specialist knowledge in the assessment and treatment of MSK patients and have an understanding of the necessary National Guidelines / Standards, as well as evidence of post graduate training in this field.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our MSK team have an excellent record of service development and successful QI projects, and you will be expected to be open to change and keen to be part of this drive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Highly developed communication skills, flexibility, good organisational and time management skills are all essential criteria. Basic IT skills are also required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to contribute to the weekend working service at Salford Royal NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to the delivery of high quality patient centred care and engagement in supervision, CPD and quality improvement activities of highly valued.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In line with the Trust’s Single Equality Scheme we welcome applications from everyone irrespective of ethnic origin, disability, age, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, disability, nationality, religion, marital status, social back ground or trade union membership. However, as members of ethnicity minority groups and individuals with disabilities are currently under-represented at this level of post, we would encourage applications from members of these groups. Appointment will be based on merit alone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Claire Guy&lt;br /&gt;Professional and Operational Lead for Physiotherapy&lt;br /&gt;Claire.guy@srft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
